        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:31PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Far East El Paso, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph, and nickel size
hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects.

Locations impacted include...
East El Paso, Far East El Paso, Horizon City, Fort Bliss, Socorro,
Sparks, Homestead Meadows, Butterfield, Agua Dulce, Fort Bliss
Northeast, Lake Way Estates, Biggs Field, and Dairyland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
